node.text:
Last but certainly not least.. “The Red Scene” … y’all I have to give this one to @normani.  This one honestly made us closer. We fought like cats and dogs about her wearing red in this scene. The looks I had confirmed for her and SIX OTHER DANCERS were black and not to mention they were already fitted and complete. It’s like she woke up with an epiphany two days before the shoot like “yea idk I really think me and the other 6 dancers should wear all red” on top of everything else we were having to figure out. I was like…sooo you want to scratch what we have? …🙄 I felt empty lol She had a really strong feeling about this red on red and she wasn’t budging. I’ll stand on my word and not budge when it comes to something I believe in but she was matching my energy.😂. I won a couple of fights with looks in this video but not this one…And she ended up being RIGHT! So now when this scene comes up we just look at each other and smirk🙄😂. She truly had a vision. 

Thank you @fashionbyreyortiz for creating this velvet and mesh body suit in a day | @sirbabajagne for deconstructing and cutting the legs all and making a Jew skirt | @brooklynprla for this red velvet pump | and @laurencebasse for making my 6 dancers look amazing! 

@yusefhairnyc this fire and Ice head piece 🔥🧊 @priscillaono red Smokey eye….insane. 

And @itsbankhead killed it once again wit this choreo. I loved working with each and everyone of you.

node.text:
@normani | This one was soo special to me….inspired by Debra Paget’s look from “The Indian Tomb”… @laureldewitt thank you for recreating this iconic look that I grew up being obsessed with. Thank you for takin out the time and reshaping the metal cups 3 times for me until we felt it was perfect! This was the last scene we shot after 3 days of shooting and the energy…you just had to be there….A moment I’d never ever forget… they danced so hard the adhesive spray started not to stick! Lol Thank you @yusefhairnyc for showing me the tricks to make this stick as long as it could lol. 

@itsbankhead @ahsiajanae soo fucking beautiful!

node.text: There seems to be a bit of confusion online on how this look came about! Allow me to explain! This full look was designed by the amazing @harryhalim_paris ! We seen the look and immediately fell in love with it! I showed it to Normani and she loved it! Two days before the shoot we found out that the look wasn’t going to make it on time, but my client had her mind and heart really set on it so we had to make it happen! We contacted @harryhalim_paris to get permission to deconstruct one of pieces of his that did make it, to have someone on ground recreate it to go with the boots (by Harry) that had already made it! The dress was a corseted dress and no one in the United States does corsets better than @garosparo ! They were able to create this dress in less than a day in NYC and overnighted it to LA! We then had the amazing @jolleson and @nathandavidadams carefully and strategically deconstruct pieces from Harry and wrap the corset dress with the same fabric to match Harry’s boots! We then gave @sarahsokolmillinery additional fabric left from Jon to create this amazing head piece! All parties were aware of where the initial design came from! Thank you to everyone who made this look happen! Always go over and beyond for your clients ❤️

node.text:
My other favorite! My take on Tomboy-chic…😩 @normani x dancers all wearing @sirbabajagne customs! Normani’s is a cropped leather blazer with power shoulders and a stacked leather boyfriend pant! This is @sirbabajagne appreciation post! You’re the BEST and you always pull through! You never say that you can’t do something and you always deliver! You had 48 hours to do 10 custom leather suits for dancers plus changes that we made to Normani’s suit PLUS working on tailoring every single look for this video, and you murdered it! We all appreciate you!
 
We paired the look with a @bryanhearns corset , @vitaly ear cuffs , and @nike Air Force ones!

We paired the dancers suits with @mahjingwong mesh corsets, @sirbabajagne rouged leather gloves! 

By far one of my favorite glam looks ever @yusefhairnyc x @priscillaono 

And @itsbankhead …..most iconic dance scene I’ve seen in a while! 😩🔥❤️ and @tanumuino understood the assignment!
